Comment_Content: In the Greek alphabet, the letter "chi" (X) is the inital letter of the word "Christ". Early Christians used the Greek letter "chi" as the symbol to represent Jesus Christ. Similarly, the letter "rho" (P) was used to represent the second part of the word "Christ." Over time, as the greek alphabet influenced other languages and cultures, the use of "X" as a suble of Christ became more widespread. The abbriviation "Xmas," for example, where "X" stands for "Christ," has been used for centuries as an abbreviation for "Christmas." Chi also means Energy.
